On Fri, 30 Aug 2002, Richard Ohran wrote:

> Greetings to the list. We have list member Giles Clement and his brother 
> Anson at my home garage in Provo after they found my name on the AIRS 
> directory. The number one cylinder on their 78 bus shows no pressure on 
> a compression test, and a leak down test  shows no pressure in the 
> cylinder with the air intermittently coming out of both intake and 
> exhaust ports as the engine is jogged. Air continually leaked through 
> the crankcase. At 60 mph, there was some activity in the cylinder but 
> not much. This was tested by pulling the spark plug wire as the vehicle 
> was moving, and noticing a change in performance.
> 
> Our best guess would be that the piston has broken rings, but oil usage 
> is not excessive... half quart in a hundred miles.
> 
> Based upon this info, any suggestions as to how to proceed from here 
> would be appreciated. Ideas on what the problem is caused by would be 
> appreciated. Also, any ideas on how to patch the vehicle so that Giles 
> can make it home to New York would also be a help.
> 
> What other tests can we perform to further isolate the problem?
> 
> Thanks for any help.
